The HER performance of CoFe, CoFe-S, and CoFe-P was tested by taking out the LSV curve. The overpotential values of the as-prepared nanocomposites are demonstrated in Fig. 3a. The CoFe-P exhibited an overpotential of 186 mV at 10 mA/cm2 which is relatively smaller than the other samples. Besides, it was recorded that CoFe-S and CoFe required 19% and 10% less potential to attain a current density of 10 mA/cm2, respectively, indicating an inferior catalytic activity. The HER in alkaline media is determined under two steps i.e., Volmer and Heyrovsky [43]. The mechanism reactions are as given by Eqs. (1)–(2).1Volmer Step:H2O+e-↔OH-+Had\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
